<p>Select a single file:</p>
<form method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data" id="singleUpload" action="default.asp?e=uploadfile"> 
  <div class="custom-file">
    <input type="file" class="custom-file-input" name="customFile" id="customFile" onchange="$('#singleUpload').submit()">
    <label class="custom-file-label" for="customFile">Choose file</label>
  </div>
</form>

<br>

<div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert">
  Security alert: this script uploads the selected file(s) in the /uploads folder. However,
  for security reasons, they are deleted right after. Check /code/asp/uploadfile.asp.
</div>

<script>
$(".custom-file-input").on("change", function() {  
  $(this).siblings(".custom-file-label").addClass("selected").html("please wait...");
});
</script>